# Copy this file to ".env" in the same folder as main.js and fill in values.
# Never commit .env (it is gitignored). If a secret was ever pasted in chat or
# committed, revoke it.
#
# NOTION_TOKEN: Create an internal Notion integration at
#   https://www.notion.so/my-integrations → "Internal Integration Secret" (starts
#   with ntn_). Then share every relevant database/page with this integration
#   (⋯ on the page → Connections → select your integration).
#
# Packaged app (.exe): put .env in the app user data folder, e.g.
#   %APPDATA%\recruit-my-english\.env
# On first run the installer copies this template there. You only need NOTION_TOKEN
# in AppData `.env`; NOTION_DATABASE_ID is taken from the app bundle (below) so each
# new build uses the DB you baked in. SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY are also
# baked into the installer when you run `npm run release` from a machine whose project
# `.env` has them set (see scripts/bake-supabase-public-env.cjs). If an older install
# shows "Supabase is not configured", add those two lines to AppData `.env` or reinstall
# a build made after baking.
# new build uses the DB you baked in — not an old seeded copy from a previous install.
# To point the installed app at a different DB instead, put NOTION_SKIP_BUNDLED_DATABASE_ID=1
# in `%APPDATA%\recruit-my-english\.env` and set NOTION_DATABASE_ID there.
#
# NOTION_DATABASE_ID: Open your database as a full page. Copy the ID from the URL path:
#   https://www.notion.so/workspace/352b1f14cd6a80f797aff1658ee608bc?v=...
#   Use this path segment — not the ?v=... value (that is a view id). 32 hex chars; hyphens optional.
#   Use the 32-character ID (with or without hyphens). The app resolves the
#   data source from this id (changing this switches databases).
#
# Teacher pay slip PDFs: match the teacher's Supabase sign-in email. Use a column named
# "Email", "Teacher email", "E-mail", etc., or put the address in any property on the row
# (title, rich text, email field, formula text). @googlemail.com and @gmail.com are treated as the same.
# Large databases: the app follows Notion pagination (100 rows per request, up to
# the API limit of about 10,000 rows per data source).
#
# Per-teacher Notion databases (admin + teacher views): run supabase/migrations/004_teacher_notion.sql
# in the Supabase SQL editor, then set public.teachers.notion_database_id (and optionally
# notion_data_source_id) per teacher. When at least one teacher has these set, the admin
# home loads one tab per teacher. If no teacher has a link, the app falls back to
# NOTION_DATABASE_ID / NOTION_DATA_SOURCE_ID above (shared database + email matching).
# The same internal integration must be invited to every teacher database.
#
# NOTION_DATA_SOURCE_ID (optional): Only if GET /v1/databases returns no data_sources
# (e.g. some wiki setups). Omit when possible — a stale value can point at the wrong DB.
# NOTION_DATA_SOURCE_ID=

NOTION_TOKEN=
NOTION_DATABASE_ID=352b1f14-cd6a-80f7-97af-f1658ee608bc
#
# Optional: seed known workspace item IDs so the workspace map (rme_workspace_map)
# returns them immediately without searching. The voice agent uses these to fetch
# pages and query database rows. If unset, the app searches at startup.
# NOTION_JOB_APPS_DB_ID=
# NOTION_ARCHIVE_DB_ID=
# NOTION_ACCOUNTING_DB_ID=
# NOTION_OUTREACH_DB_ID=
# NOTION_RECRUITING_MSGS_DB_ID=
# NOTION_AUDIT_PAGE_ID=
# NOTION_MISSION_CONTROL_ID=
# NOTION_PORTAL_CODES_ID=

# Sign-in uses Supabase Auth (email + password in the app). Enable the Email
# provider under Authentication → Providers. For quick local testing, turn off
# "Confirm email" on that Email provider screen so new users can sign in
# immediately without opening an inbox link. The authorized admin email is set in
# auth-store.js (ALLOWED_ADMIN_EMAIL), not in .env.
#
# In Project Settings → API, set SUPABASE_URL to the project URL and
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY to the anon / public client key (legacy JWT starting with
# eyJ… or a publishable key if your project uses that — same field the JS client expects).
# Use these exact names (not NEXT_PUBLIC_* — that is for Next.js only).
# URL must include the scheme: https://YOUR_REF.supabase.co (or http://127.0.0.1:54321 for
# Supabase CLI local). A missing https:// or a broken line in the anon key often shows as
# "Failed to fetch" in the sign-in form.
# Leave blank here; put real values only in your private .env (not committed).
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
#
# One-time (dev machine only): upload wallpapers to Storage and upsert
# `payslip_app_backgrounds` after running supabase/migrations/014_payslip_app_backgrounds_storage.sql
#   npm run sync:app-backgrounds
# Requires SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (never ship this in the desktop app).
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
#
# If the app reports that public.teachers is missing: open Supabase Dashboard →
# SQL, paste and run supabase/migrations/001_teachers.sql for this project.
# For teacher profile fields and avatar uploads, also run 002_teacher_profile.sql.
# For the admin Teachers tab (list everyone), run 003_admin_teacher_directory.sql
# For teacher payslip ↔ admin Notion row id matching, run 011_teacher_notion_person_resolve.sql.

# --- Desktop release (your build PC only — not for teachers' .env) ---
# One command: build Windows installer + upload to GitHub Releases + latest.yml
#   1. Bump "version" in package.json (e.g. 1.0.1 → 1.0.2)
#   2. Quit the installed app / npm start (avoids EBUSY on node_modules)
#   3. PowerShell:  $env:GH_TOKEN = "github_pat_..."   (repo + Releases write)
#   4.            npm run release
# Uploads to https://github.com/Ayaaz777/Teachers-Portal/releases
# Assets: Recruit-My-English-Setup-x.y.z.exe, latest.yml, .blockmap
# Local build only (no upload): npm run dist
# Portable (no auto-update): npm run dist:portable
# Optional: RME_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=1 in a teacher's .env to turn off checks.
#
# --- Voice agent (admin dashboard — local STT/TTS + Claude API) ---
# Voice stack (one-time): npm run setup:voice
# Downloads into tools/voice/ and writes these paths into .env:
# RME_WHISPER_BIN=<project>\tools\voice\whisper\Release\whisper-cli.exe
# RME_WHISPER_MODEL=<project>\tools\voice\models\ggml-small.en.bin
#
# Persistent GPU whisper-server (cuBLAS CUDA build — fastest for Turing+ GPUs)
# RME_WHISPER_SERVER_BIN=<project>\tools\voice\whisper-cuda\whisper-server.exe
# Fast model used by the persistent server (ggml-base.en.bin for ~400ms utterances)
# RME_WHISPER_MODEL_FAST=<project>\tools\voice\models\ggml-base.en.bin
# Fallback accurate model when fast model is missing (ggml-small.en.bin)
# RME_WHISPER_MODEL_ACCURATE=<project>\tools\voice\models\ggml-small.en.bin
# RME_WHISPER_SERVER_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8780
# RME_WHISPER_SERVER_GPU=auto
# RME_WHISPER_FLASH_ATTN=1
# RME_WHISPER_BEAM_SIZE=1
# RME_WHISPER_BEST_OF=1
# Cartesia Sonic TTS (REST API)
# CARTESIA_API_KEY=
# RME_CARTESIA_MODEL=sonic-3.5
# RME_CARTESIA_VOICE_ID=
# RME_CARTESIA_SAMPLE_RATE=44100
# Anthropic Messages API (streaming brain — only paid component)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929
# Hold-to-talk brain model
# RME_VOICE_ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929
# RME_VOICE_MAX_TOKENS=700
# RME_VOICE_ACK=0
# RME_VOICE_ACK_TEXT=Okay.
# Faster STT model override (download ggml-base.en.bin into tools/voice/models/)
# RME_WHISPER_MODEL_FAST=<project>\tools\voice\models\ggml-base.en.bin
# Set 1 to use ANTHROPIC_MODEL / pickClaudeModel routing for voice instead
# RME_VOICE_USE_MAIN_MODEL=0
# Model for short non-question turns
# RME_ANTHROPIC_MODEL_FAST=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
# Prompt caching on system prompt (set 0 to disable)
# RME_CLAUDE_PROMPT_CACHE=1
#
# If Notion returns 401 "API token is invalid": the secret may have been
# refreshed, or you pasted the wrong value. Use only the integration's
# "Internal Integration Secret" from my-integrations — not an OAuth client secret.
